Process Document – Monitoring and Managing
Aging Pending Sub-Issues
Model Risk Management Committee (MRMC) | MRO Workstream

Background and Problem Statement
Pending Sub-Issues within the model risk inventory were aging for extended periods without disposition or resolution. This represents a material risk to the organization and is directly tied to an active audit issue. Timely monitoring, proactive outreach, and structured escalation of aging Sub-Issues are therefore critical compliance obligations for the MRMC / MRO team.
This process document establishes a repeatable, policy-aligned monthly framework for identifying, monitoring, and escalating aging pending Sub-Issues in ServiceNow (SNOW), ensuring no Sub-Issue exceeds its tier-based threshold without documented action.

1. Purpose
This document provides a detailed, step-by-step process for the identification, proactive monitoring, and escalation management of aging pending Sub-Issues within the MRMC framework. The process is designed to:

• Prevent Sub-Issues from breaching tier-based aging thresholds through early warning outreach.
• Ensure timely escalation where thresholds have been crossed.
• Support quarterly Sub-Issue review obligations under MRMC Policy Procedure Section 2.2.8.
• Address the active audit issue related to aging pending Sub-Issues through a structured, documented monthly cadence.
2. Scope
In Scope:
• All Sub-Issues in the MRM Issue/Sub-Issue inventory in SNOW currently in a "Pending" status (including Pending Review and related pending sub-statuses).
• Sub-Issues linked to Tier 1, Tier 2, Tier 3, and Tier 4 models, with differentiated aging thresholds applied per tier.
• Sub-Issues approaching or having exceeded their defined aging threshold requiring proactive communication or formal escalation.
Out of Scope:
• Sub-Issues that are formally closed with documented closure rationale.
• Formal Issues (as distinct from Sub-Issues) managed under the Issue escalation process.
3. Tier-Based Aging Thresholds
Aging thresholds for pending Sub-Issues are applied based on model tier designation as follows:
